</p><p>All of the 40 patients completed the 17-day trial. Of the 40 patients, 20 (50%) received 8 mg of buprenorphine and 20 (50%) received 40 mg of methadone. Table&#x000a0;<xref rid="Tab1" ref-type="table">1</xref> displays the demographic characteristics of both groups.<table-wrap id="Tab1"><label>Table 1</label><caption><p>Demographic characteristics of the two study groups</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th colspan="2"/><th>Methadone (<italic>n</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;20)</th><th>Buprenorphine (<italic>n</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;20)</th><th>Total</th><th>Significance</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan="2">Age, years, mean&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;SD</td><td>31.2&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;9.04</td><td>34.35&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;9.65</td><td>32.78&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;9.37</td><td>
